REPLICATOR MANAGER MAIN MENU

This menu is used to select a task to manage Ingres Replicator.  The
screen shows the database name and database number accessed with
Replicator Manager, in the upper right-hand corner.  It also displays
the Replicator version identifier.

The following choices are available:

        SELECTION       ALLOWS YOU TO
        ---------       -------------
        Configuration   Access the Configuration Menu which contains
                        selections required to configure Replicator.

        Monitor         Start and stop the Replicator Servers, monitor
                        replication activities occurring on this
                        database, and send database events to servers
                        running against this database.

        Resolver        Access the Resolver Reports Menu to produce
                        reports to aid in troubleshooting, collision
                        resolution, and configuring Replicator.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        Select          Choose the currently highlighted option.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        Quit            Exit Replicator Manager.
